The paper deals with bounding the rate of bit-stuffing encoders for 2-D constraints, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS) as well as algorithms and complexity (cs.DC). The use of linear programming suggests that the paper may also be relevant to optimization and control (cs.SI) and computational complexity (cs.CC).
